                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3736mn6b/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">As to my future course in the holy<lb/> office upon which I am about\n                to <hi rend=\"underline\">re</hi>-enter,<lb/> I will say nothing; you know my\n                views,<lb/> principles &amp; convictions—the cause of<lb/> the Jews &amp; Judaism\n                shall never suffer<lb/> shame &amp; disgrace at my hand!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Believe me to remain, as ever,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours &amp;c</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">M Mayer</persName>\n            </p>\n            <div>\n                <p>\n                    <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_20_21.pdf\">The above text refers to Occident\n                        Volume 20 No. 21 page 47. Click here to view.</ref>\n                </p>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
